https://civitai.com/models/420163

PROMPTS
-------
Using the same prompt for both models is usually sufficient. However:
  * If the main prompt is very long, you may need a shorter one for SD15.
  * If the image quality is poor, adjust the SD15 prompt as per the model author's recommendations.
 
STEPS & CFG
-----------
Currently, I've only been experimenting with photorealistic images and using Photon as a refiner. The following parameters have worked quite well, though you may need to adjust these values for other styles and models:

  - PixArt steps  :  16
  - SD15 end step :  26
  - CFG scale     : 4.0
 
IMAGE SIZE
----------
I'm pushing PixArt beyond its recommended image size. However, if quality suffers, it's best to stick to the values provided by PixArt's authors. For the 1K model:
 
    9:21 =  640 x 1536
    9:16 =  768 x 1344
    4:5  =  896 x 1152
    2:3  =  832 x 1216
    1:1  = 1024 x 1024
    3:2  = 1216 x  832
    5:4  =  896 x 1152
   21:9  = 1536 x  640
   16:9  = 1344 x  768

OUTPUT IMAGES
-------------
The generated images will be automatically stored in the folder:
    <your-comfyui-directory>/output/abominable
 
REQUIRED NODES
--------------
You need to have 'ComfyUI_ExtraModels' installed.
Here's how to do it on Linux in four simple steps:
  > cd <your-comfyui-directory>
  > cd custom_nodes
  > git clone https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI_ExtraModels
  > pip install -r requirements.txt

Note 1: Running pip may require activating the virtual env used to run ComfyUI.
Note 2: Windows users can refer to the installation methods on the project GitHub Page:
        - https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI_ExtraModels?tab=readme-ov-file#installation
Note 3: ComfyUI_ExtraModels has dependencies and requirements on which it heavily relies.
        Therefore, it might be more convenient to install it using ComfyUI Manager.
        - https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Manager

REQUIRED FILES
--------------
You also need to have the following 6 files locally:

  from: https://github.com/PixArt-alpha/PixArt-sigma?tab=readme-ov-file#-available-models
